{
  "local_port": 45516,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which type of questions in asp.net practical interview?",
  "response": "In an ASP.NET practical interview, you can expect a mix of theoretical and hands-on coding questions. The types of questions typically focus on your understanding of ASP.NET concepts, architecture, and your ability to implement solutions. Here are some common types of questions and topics:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Basic ASP.NET Concepts**\n- What is ASP.NET? How is it different from ASP?\n- Explain the page lifecycle in ASP.NET.\n- What are the main components of an ASP.NET application?\n- Difference between Web Forms and MVC in ASP.NET.\n\n---\n\n### **2. ASP.NET Core vs ASP.NET Framework**\n- What are the key differences between ASP.NET Core and ASP.NET Framework?\n- Why should you choose ASP.NET Core over the Framework?\n- Explain middleware in ASP.NET Core.\n- How does dependency injection work in ASP.NET Core?\n\n---\n\n### **3. Web Forms (if applicable)**\n- Differences between Server Controls and HTML Controls.\n- Explain ViewState and its purpose.\n- How does postback work in Web Forms?\n- What is the role of the `Page_Load` event?\n\n---\n\n### **4. ASP.NET MVC**\n- Explain the MVC architecture.\n- What is Routing in ASP.NET MVC? How do you define custom routes?\n- Differences between ViewBag, ViewData, and TempData.\n- How to implement authentication and authorization in MVC?\n- What are Action Filters, and how do you use them?\n- Explain the role of the Model, View, and Controller in MVC.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Web API**\n- Difference between WCF and Web API.\n- How to create and consume a Web API in ASP.NET?\n- What is REST, and how is it implemented in ASP.NET Web API?\n- How to implement authentication in Web API (e.g., JWT)?\n\n---\n\n### **6. Entity Framework (EF) and Database Integration**\n- What is Entity Framework? Explain Code First, Database First, and Model First approaches.\n- How to perform CRUD operations using EF in ASP.NET?\n- Difference between LINQ and SQL queries.\n- How to handle database migrations in EF Core?\n\n---\n\n### **7. Security**\n- How to prevent SQL Injection in ASP.NET?\n- What is Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) and how to prevent it?\n- Explain authentication and authorization in ASP.NET.\n- How to implement Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)?\n\n---\n\n### **8. State Management**\n- What are the different ways to manage state in ASP.NET (e.g., Session, Cookies, ViewState)?\n- Difference between Session and Cookies.\n- How to use Application State and Session State effectively?\n\n---\n\n### **9. Asynchronous Programming**\n- How to implement asynchronous programming in ASP.NET?\n- Difference between `async` and `await` in C#.\n\n---\n\n### **10. Deployment and Configuration**\n- How to deploy an ASP.NET application to IIS?\n- What is the `web.config` file? How is it used in ASP.NET?\n- Difference between `appsettings.json` in ASP.NET Core and `web.config` in ASP.NET Framework.\n\n---\n\n### **11. Practical Coding Tasks**\n- Create a simple CRUD application using ASP.NET MVC or Web API.\n- Implement pagination in an ASP.NET application.\n- Write a LINQ query to fetch data from a database.\n- Implement user authentication and authorization in an ASP.NET Core application.\n- Write code to handle exceptions globally in ASP.NET Core.\n- Create a custom middleware in ASP.NET Core.\n\n---\n\n### **12. Debugging and Troubleshooting**\n- How do you troubleshoot a slow-performing ASP.NET application?\n- What are common errors in ASP.NET applications, and how do you resolve them?\n\n---\n\n### **13. Advanced Topics (Depending on Experience)**\n- Explain SignalR and its use cases.\n- What is Blazor? How is it different from MVC?\n- How to implement caching in ASP.NET?\n- Explain the concept of Dependency Injection and its benefits.\n\n---\n\n### Tips for Preparation:\n- Practice building small projects in ASP.NET MVC or Core.\n- Understand the architectural differences between frameworks.\n- Be prepared to explain your code and design decisions.\n- Review common interview coding tasks and debugging scenarios.\n\nGood luck with your interview! \ud83d\ude80",
  "temperature": 1.0,
